    <p style="font-family: 'Oxygen', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-weight:400; font-size: 14px; line-height:18px; margin:0 0 15px 0; padding:0; color:#000000;">Dear Colleague</p>
	<p style="font-family: 'Oxygen', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-weight:400; font-size: 14px; line-height:18px; margin:0 0 15px 0; padding:0; color:#000000;">When you create a course in the Clarity Course Builder, who else can see or edit that course? Is it shared with your colleagues or can only you do anything to it? At present, all teachers in an account can see and edit all courses. But we’ve just added a way to control this using permissions.</p>
	<p style="font-family: 'Oxygen', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-weight:400; font-size: 14px; line-height:18px; margin:0 0 15px 0; padding:0; color:#000000;">These are the new settings for other teachers in your group or account:<br/>
1) <b>Publishers</b> can see the course and schedule their students to do it. They can’t change anything. This is the setting for a new course.<br/>
2) <b>Collaborators</b> can make changes to the course and schedule their students to do it. They can’t delete the course.<br/>
3) <b>Locked</b>. Nobody can edit the course until you unlock it. Useful for protecting completed courses from accidental change.<br/>
</p>
	<p style="font-family: 'Oxygen', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-weight:400; font-size: 14px; line-height:18px; margin:0 0 15px 0; padding:0; color:#000000;">You can find more details from this <a href="http://youtu.be/vIU-DsawnK4">video</a>, or from the Course Builder reference on our support site.</p>
	<p style="font-family: 'Oxygen', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-weight:400; font-size: 14px; line-height:18px; margin:0 0 15px 0; padding:0; color:#000000;"> Your existing courses have all teachers set as collaborators as this keeps things the way they are. You only need to take action if you want to stop other people editing them. Please do email if you have any questions or concerns.</p>
